# YouTube to Apple Music Bridge - Cursor Rules

You are an expert TypeScript/React developer working on a Chrome extension that bridges YouTube music discovery to Apple Music playback.

## Project Context

This is a Chrome extension that:

- Detects music videos on YouTube using content scripts
- Uses AI (OpenAI) to enhance song matching accuracy
- Opens songs directly in Apple Music app (native) or web player
- Built with React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + Vite
- Features intelligent caching system with user confirmation
- Provides seamless YouTube-to-Apple Music workflow

## Code Style & Standards

### TypeScript

- Use strict TypeScript with explicit types
- Prefer interfaces over type aliases for object shapes
- Use string enums for constants
- Always handle async/await with proper error handling
- Use generic constraints appropriately

### React

- Use functional components only
- Define props interfaces for all components
- Use React.memo for performance-critical components
- Extract complex logic into custom hooks
- Follow hooks rules (no conditional hooks)

### Styling

- Use Tailwind CSS classes primarily
- Create semantic component classes in CSS when needed
- Use the established color palette (apple-red, apple-pink, etc.)
- Ensure responsive design for popup constraints
- Use glass-effect and gradient classes from existing styles

### Extension-Specific

- Always check DOM elements exist before accessing
- Use proper message passing between scripts
- Handle Chrome API errors gracefully
- Clean up event listeners and observers
- Use debouncing for frequent operations
- **NEVER automatically close Chrome alerts/prompts - let user decide**

## Architecture Patterns

### File Organization

```
src/
├── popup/           # React popup UI
├── background/      # Service worker
├── content/         # Content scripts
├── utils/           # Shared utilities
├── types/           # TypeScript definitions
└── styles/          # Tailwind CSS
```

### Message Passing

- Use typed message interfaces from `src/types/index.ts`
- Always handle message errors with try/catch
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Use centralized message routing in background script

### Error Handling

- Always provide fallbacks for AI features
- Log errors with context for debugging
- Show user-friendly status messages
- Never expose internal errors to users

## Key Components

### YouTube Detection (`src/content/youtube-detector.ts`)

- Monitors YouTube pages for music videos
- Uses MutationObserver for SPA navigation
- Extracts metadata (title, artist, channel)
- Calculates confidence scores for matches
- **CRITICAL**: Clear `currentVideoData` on URL changes to prevent stale data

### Apple Music Integration (`src/utils/appleMusicUtils.ts`)

- Tries native app first, falls back to web
- Uses URL schemes: `music://` and `itmss://`
- Handles platform detection (macOS/iOS)
- Optimizes search queries
- **CRITICAL**: NEVER automatically close tabs or alerts - user has full control
- **CRITICAL**: Use ONLY `itmss://` scheme to prevent prompt auto-closing

### AI Enhancement (`src/utils/aiUtils.ts`)

- Optional OpenAI integration for better matching
- Always has rule-based fallback
- Handles API errors gracefully
- Uses structured prompts for consistency

### Background Service (`src/background/background.ts`)

- Centralized message handling
- Settings management
- Tab tracking for Apple Music
- Notification system
- **CRITICAL**: Store confirmation data immediately - no delays

### Caching System (`src/utils/cacheUtils.ts`)

- Persistent YouTube ID to Apple Music song ID mapping
- Uses `chrome.storage.local` for persistence
- Requires user confirmation before saving matches
- Provides cache statistics and export functionality

## Development Workflow

### Building

- Use `npm run dev` for development with watching
- Use `npm run build` for production builds
- Load `dist/` folder in Chrome extensions
- Test on different YouTube video types

### Code Quality

- Run `npm run type-check` for TypeScript errors
- Run `npm run lint` for code quality
- Follow existing patterns and conventions
- Write clear commit messages

### Testing

- Test on official music videos, covers, live performances
- Test AI enhancement with and without API key
- Test native app opening on macOS
- Test error scenarios (network issues, invalid videos)
- **CRITICAL**: Test that Chrome alerts never close automatically

## Common Patterns

### Safe DOM Access

```typescript
private async waitForElement(selector: string, timeout = 5000): Promise<Element> {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    const element = document.querySelector(selector);
    if (element) {
      resolve(element);
      return;
    }

    const observer = new MutationObserver(() => {
      const element = document.querySelector(selector);
      if (element) {
        observer.disconnect();
        resolve(element);
      }
    });

    observer.observe(document.body, { childList: true, subtree: true });
    setTimeout(() => {
      observer.disconnect();
      reject(new Error(`Element ${selector} not found`));
    }, timeout);
  });
}
```

### Message Handling

```typescript
chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener(
  (message: ExtensionMessage, sender, sendResponse) => {
    switch (message.type) {
      case "MUSIC_DETECTED":
        this.handleMusicDetected(message.data);
        sendResponse({ success: true });
        break;
      default:
        sendResponse({ success: false, error: "Unknown message type" });
    }
    return true; // Keep channel open for async
  },
);
```

### AI with Fallback

```typescript
static async enhanceSearchWithAI(musicData: MusicData, apiKey?: string): Promise<AISearchResponse> {
  if (!apiKey) {
    return this.enhanceSearchRuleBased(musicData);
  }

  try {
    return await this.callOpenAI(musicData, apiKey);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('AI enhancement failed, falling back:', error);
    return this.enhanceSearchRuleBased(musicData);
  }
}
```

### User Control Pattern (CRITICAL)

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Let user decide
static async openDirectSong(musicData: MusicData) {
  const schemes = [`itmss://music.apple.com/us/song/${songId}`];

  for (const scheme of schemes) {
    const tab = await chrome.tabs.create({ url: scheme, active: true });
    console.log(`🎯 Opened ${scheme} - user has full control`);
    return true; // Success - let user handle the prompt
  }
}

// ❌ WRONG: Automatic closing
setTimeout(() => {
  chrome.tabs.remove(tab.id!); // NEVER DO THIS
}, 500);
```

### Cache Confirmation Pattern

```typescript
// Return object with confirmation data for background script to handle
return {
  url: appleMusicUrl,
  needsConfirmation: true,
  confirmationData: {
    youtubeId,
    youtubeTitle: `${artist} - ${songTitle}`,
    appleMusicArtist: song.artistName,
    appleMusicSong: song.trackName,
  },
  isCached: false,
};
```

## Performance Guidelines

- Use debouncing for frequent operations (video detection)
- Clean up observers and listeners on component unmount
- Minimize memory usage in background scripts
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Avoid blocking the main thread

## Security & Privacy

- Never hardcode API keys (except Supabase anon key - see Community Database)
- Process data locally when possible
- Don't collect user behavior data
- Use chrome.storage.sync for settings
- Validate all external inputs

### Community Database Configuration

- **Centralized Approach**: Use pre-configured Supabase credentials for community database
- **Anon Key Safety**: Supabase anon keys are designed to be public and safe to expose
- **No Environment Variables**: Don't use .env files for community database credentials
- **Documentation**: Keep setup guides focused on zero-config for end users
- **Developer Override**: Allow developers to configure their own instance via `src/config/supabase.ts`

## User Experience

- Provide clear status messages
- Show confidence scores for transparency
- Allow manual override of automatic behavior
- Graceful degradation when features fail
- Respect user preferences and settings
- **CRITICAL**: Never interfere with user choice on Chrome prompts

## Critical Rules (NEVER BREAK THESE)

### 1. User Control Over Chrome Prompts

- **NEVER** automatically close Chrome alerts/prompts
- **NEVER** use setTimeout to close tabs
- **NEVER** implement fallback schemes that auto-trigger
- User must have complete control over "Open Apple Music?" prompts

### 2. Cache Confirmation System

- Store confirmation data **immediately** - no delays
- Show confirmation UI **directly in popup** - no separate windows
- Use `currentPendingConfirmation` pattern for single confirmation
- Clear confirmation data after user action

### 3. YouTube Detection Reliability

- Clear `currentVideoData = null` on URL changes
- Handle "Extension context invalidated" errors gracefully
- Use MutationObserver for SPA navigation detection
- Debounce video detection to prevent spam

### 4. Apple Music URL Schemes

- Use **ONLY** `itmss://music.apple.com/us/song/${songId}` for direct songs
- Extract song ID cleanly: `directLink.split("/song/")[1].split("?")[0]`
- Fallback to search only when direct song fails
- Aggressive title cleaning: remove everything from first `(` or `[`

### 5. Message Passing Architecture

- Use typed interfaces from `src/types/index.ts`
- Handle `chrome.runtime.lastError` in all Chrome API calls
- Return objects from utils, not direct Chrome messages
- Background script orchestrates all Chrome API interactions

## When Adding Features

1. Update TypeScript types first
2. Follow existing architectural patterns
3. Add proper error handling
4. Update documentation
5. Test thoroughly across different scenarios
6. Consider performance impact
7. Maintain backward compatibility
8. **NEVER** add automatic closing logic

## Common Issues & Solutions

- **Build errors**: Check ES module syntax, ensure proper imports
- **Extension loading**: Verify manifest paths match build output
- **Message passing**: Always handle chrome.runtime.lastError
- **DOM access**: Use waitForElement pattern for dynamic content
- **API failures**: Always provide fallbacks and user feedback
- **Chrome prompts closing**: Remove ALL automatic closing logic
- **Stale video data**: Clear cache on URL changes

## Project-Specific Patterns

### iTunes API Integration

```typescript
// Use iTunes API for song ID, but create Apple Music URLs
const iTunesUrl = `https://itunes.apple.com/search?term=${encodeURIComponent(
  query,
)}&media=music&entity=song&limit=1`;
const appleMusicUrl = `https://music.apple.com/us/song/${song.trackId}`;
```

### Title Optimization

```typescript
// Aggressive cleaning for better matching
const optimizedQuery = title
  .replace(/\s*\(.*$/gi, "") // Remove everything from first (
  .replace(/\s*\[.*$/gi, "") // Remove everything from first [
  .replace(/\s*(official\s+)?(music\s+)?video\s*/gi, "")
  .replace(/\s*(ft\.?|feat\.?|featuring)\s+.*/gi, "");
```

### Extension Context Error Handling

```typescript
try {
  await chrome.runtime.sendMessage(message);
} catch (error) {
  if (error.message.includes("Extension context invalidated")) {
    console.log("🔄 Extension reloaded - please refresh YouTube page");
    return;
  }
  throw error;
}
```

Remember: Prioritize user privacy, performance, and reliability. When in doubt, choose the safer, more conservative approach that gives users maximum control.
